== Sports ==
Sumy was formerly home to the [[Ukrainian First League]] [[Football (soccer)|football]] team [[FC Spartak Sumy]] (now defunct).

The [[Ukrainian Premier League]] [[Football (soccer)|football]] club [[FC Kharkiv]] are currently leasing the city's state-of-the-art [[Yuvileiny Stadium]].

== Weather and climate ==
Sumy is located in the northeastern part of Ukraine. So its weather is similar to that in Kharkov.
Sumy's climate is moderate [[Continental climate|continental]]: cold and snowy winters, and hot summers. The seasonal average temperatures are not too cold in winter, not too hot in summer: {{convert|-6.9|<U+00B0>C|<U+00B0>F}} in January, and {{convert|20.3|<U+00B0>C|<U+00B0>F}} in July. The average rainfall totals {{convert|513|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} per year, with the most in June and July.
